<asp:Content ID="Content2" ContentPlaceHolderID="MainContent" runat="server">
    <div style="padding: 0 25px; text-align: justify">
        <div class="title">
            
                Privacy
        </div>
        <p class="Default">
            <span lang="EN-AU">
                <o:p>
        &nbsp;</o:p>
            </span>
        </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span lang="EN-AU">Inner East Community Health
                Service (IECHS) is committed to protecting your privacy.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <span lang="EN-AU">This privacy statement details what personal information we collect,
                how we use it, who has access to it and what your privacy choices are.<span>&nbsp;
                </span>It applies to information supplied and collected by the Healthy Boroondara
                Club.<span>&nbsp; </span>
                <o:p>
        </o:p>
            </span>
        </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <span lang="EN-AU">There is a separate policy for personal information collected by
                Inner East Community Health Service which is not connected with the personal information
                held by the Healthy Boroondara Club.<span>&nbsp; </span>
                <o:p>
        </o:p>
            </span>
        </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span lang="EN-AU">Collection of your personal
                information<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <span lang="EN-AU">The Healthy Boroondara Club may collect information that you provide
                when you interact with it. The Club may also collect information about your interactions
                with the activities listed by the Club and rewards earned.<span>&nbsp; </span>The
                Club does not collect information about you from any other sources.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span lang="EN-AU">How we use your personal
                information<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <span lang="EN-AU">We collect and use your personal information to improve our service
                and provide you with information that may be of interest to you.<span>&nbsp; </span>
                We do not share your identified personal information with any organisation outside
                the Healthy Boroondara Club without specifically asking for your permission on a
                case by case basis. We may use your information to contact you by various means
                on an ongoing basis, subject to you exercising your privacy rights and selections
                below.<span>&nbsp; </span>Your permission will be sought if other organisations
                wish to contact you using the personal information that we hold.
                <o:p>
        </o:p>
            </span>
        </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <span lang="EN-AU">We may use your personal information in a de-identified way for research
                and analysis. Your name or other identifying data will not be used.
                <o:p>
        </o:p>
            </span>
        </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span lang="EN-AU">How we secure your personal
                data<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <span lang="EN-AU">Your data is held securely and personal details are encrypted and
                identifying features stored separately to the data.
                <o:p>
        </o:p>
            </span>
        </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span lang="EN-AU">Our website<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <span lang="EN-AU">Our website may use cookies occasionally to allow our server to interact
                with your device effectively. The cookie stores some of your information to maintain
                continuity of browsing.<span>&nbsp; </span>If you reject a cookie it may affect
                how well you can interact with the web site.<span>&nbsp; </span>Cookies can easily
                be deleted at the end of a session.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <span lang="EN-AU">Our website contains links to other sites.<span>&nbsp; </span>We
                are not responsible for the privacy practices and policies of those sites and recommend
                that you review their privacy policies.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span lang="EN-AU">Your privacy rights<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">
            <span lang="EN-AU">We respect your right to privacy and also the rights you have under
                privacy laws to access and correct information that we may collect about you.<span>&nbsp;
                </span>You also have the right to decline communications from us.<span>&nbsp; </span>
                To contact us please use the following email: <a href="mailto:info@iechs.org.au"><span>
                    info@iechs.org.au</span></a> or ring 03 9420 9114 or use the contact page on
                the following website: <a href="http://www.iechs.com.au/"><span>http://www.iechs.com.au/</span></a>
                <o:p>
        </o:p>
            </span>
        </p>
